 safe XPath with predicates\n    teams = doc.xpath(\"//team[name=$name]/members/member/name/text()\", name=team_name)\n    \n    if not teams:\n        abort(404)\n    \n    html = \"<ul>\"\n    for member in teams:\n        html += f\"<li>{member}</li>\"\n    html += \"</ul>\"\n    \n    return html\n```\n\nI need to avoid XPath injection by using parameterized queries instead of string formatting. The XPath expression uses a variable placeholder `$name` with the actual value passed as a keyword argument, which safely handles the team name lookup without concatenation risks. html += \"</ul>\"\n    \n    return html\n```\n\nUsing XPath variables with lxml is the proper solution here. The `xpath()` method accepts keyword arguments that get safely substituted into the query, preventing injection attacks. I can construct the query to directly extract member names in one call rather than navigating through multiple steps.\n\nThe function handles the key requirements: extracting the team_name parameter, validating it exists, safely querying for matching members, returning a 404 if none are found, and formatting the results as an HTML list.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5112,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5112},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"33ec9b2a-fcfd-4ea6-a7d3-38a5bf5c7f18","uuid":"71a01613-ae2f-4b9c-86ea-3b0af8278a1e","request_id":"req_011CbdNefrCkRncvrdMBQ3vS"}
